LAGOS  – Operatives of Ogun State Command of the Depart­ment of State Security Ser­vice (DSS), have arrested three more persons in con­nection with the previous ar­rest of an alleged notorious land grabber and suspected killer, Elijah Adeogun aka ‘Killer’. Adeogun was earlier ar­rested in the Obasanjo area of the state by DSS opera­tives over alleged involve­ment in land related crises and killings in the state. Following his arrest, op­eratives had declared man­hunt for suspected members of his gang. A source, who was privy to the arrest of the three suspects, identified them as Adeshina Busari aka Shiner, Quadri Anisere aka Vulga and Bolarinwa Yussuf aka Igun . Elijah was nabbed weeks back, following a petition by a family, Adelupo Family of Ipetu Baba Ode. The family in the petition, alleged that he was responsi­ble for the death of two per­sons, Monday Eredua on the 17th of November 2021 and Moruf Babalola on the 26th of May, 2021.